benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Retrieve payment custom fields

covered: Valid Request scenarios for successful retrieval (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC16, TC18, TC19, TC22, TC23)
Handling of invalid inputs and security tests (TC06, TC13, TC14, TC20, TC21, TC25)
Error/dependency handling and resilience (TC10, TC17, TC07)
Data/state coverage including empty and partially populated databases (TC04, TC19, TC22, TC23)
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets.
Caching Behavior: No tests checking for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
403 Forbidden scenarios not specifically tested (beyond general 401).
Rate Limiting / throttling tests not present.
Performance/latency tests beyond a single 500ms target (TC12) not covered for broader scenarios or under load.
Granular validation for audit parameter values (beyond INVALID in TC25) not exhaustively covered.
More explicit 502/503 coverage around downstream/dependent services beyond TC17 and TC10 could be expanded.
recommendations: Add pagination-focused tests to verify proper handling of large datasets and potential page-based responses (limits, offsets, next/prev links).
Introduce tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and client-side caching behavior.
Add explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios to verify authorization levels beyond 401.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under high concurrency.
Expand audit parameter validation with additional invalid values and boundary conditions, plus NONE/explicit NONE coverage in various paths.
Enhance resilience tests by adding more scenarios around dependent services failures (e.g., repeated 502/503, retries, circuit breakers).
